White House Press Secretary Jen Psaki provided an update on the tornadoes that recently hit the central United States. President Biden has been receiving regular briefings on the situation and will travel to Kentucky to survey storm damage. The President has approved emergency disaster and major disaster declarations for Kentucky, making federal assistance available to affected individuals and communities. FEMA has been providing resources and assistance to impacted areas. Psaki also announced that the President will sign an executive order aimed at improving the delivery of government services to the American people. The order outlines agency actions to simplify access to government services and benefits. Psaki highlighted the importance of the Child Tax Credit and emphasized the need to pass the Build Back Better bill to extend it. She also addressed questions about releasing frozen funds to Afghanistan and the ongoing discussions with Senator Joe Manchin on the Build Back Better bill. Psaki mentioned that the President will continue to address climate change and extreme weather events.